Enum UnitType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<UnitType>
      • bwapi.UnitType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<UnitType>

    public enum UnitType
extends Enum<UnitType>
    The UnitType is used to get information about a particular type of unit, such as its cost, build time, weapon, hit points, abilities, etc.
    See Also:
    Unit.getType()

        Checks if this unit type is a refinery. A refinery is a structure that is placed on top of a @geyser . Refinery types are @refinery , @extractor , and @assimilator.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is a refinery, and false if it is not.

      • isWorker

        public boolean isWorker()
        Checks if this unit type is a worker unit. Worker units can harvest resources and build structures. Worker unit types include the @SCV , @probe, and @drone.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is a worker, and false if it is not.

      • requiresPsi

        public boolean requiresPsi()
        Checks if this structure is powered by a psi field. Structures powered by psi can only be placed near a @Pylon. If the @Pylon is destroyed, then this unit will lose power.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type can only be placed in a psi field, false otherwise.

      • requiresCreep

        public boolean requiresCreep()
        Checks if this structure must be placed on @Zerg creep.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type requires creep, false otherwise.

      • isTwoUnitsInOneEgg

        public boolean isTwoUnitsInOneEgg()
        Checks if this unit type spawns two units when being hatched from an @Egg. This is only applicable to @Zerglings and @Scourges.
        Returns:
        true if morphing this unit type will spawn two of them, and false if only one is spawned.

      • isBurrowable

        public boolean isBurrowable()
        Checks if this unit type has the capability to use the @Burrow technology when it is researched.

        The @Lurker can burrow even without researching the ability.

        Returns:
        true if this unit can use the @Burrow ability, and false otherwise.
        See Also:
        TechType.Burrowing

      • isCloakable

        public boolean isCloakable()
        Checks if this unit type has the capability to use a cloaking ability when it is researched. This applies only to @Wraiths and @Ghosts, and does not include units which are permanently cloaked.
        Returns:
        true if this unit has a cloaking ability, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        hasPermanentCloak(), TechType.Cloaking_Field, TechType.Personnel_Cloaking

      • isBuilding

        public boolean isBuilding()
        Checks if this unit is a structure. This includes @Mineral_Fields and @Vespene_Geysers.
        Returns:
        true if this unit is a building, and false otherwise.

      • isAddon

        public boolean isAddon()
        Checks if this unit is an add-on. Add-ons are attachments used by some @Terran structures such as the @Comsat_Station.
        Returns:
        true if this unit is an add-on, and false otherwise.

      • isFlyingBuilding

        public boolean isFlyingBuilding()
        Checks if this structure has the capability to use the lift-off command.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is a flyable building, false otherwise.

      • isNeutral

        public boolean isNeutral()
        Checks if this unit type is a neutral type, such as critters and resources.
        Returns:
        true if this unit is intended to be neutral, and false otherwise.

      • isHero

        public boolean isHero()
        Checks if this unit type is a hero. Heroes are types that the player cannot obtain normally, and are identified by the white border around their icon when selected with a group.

        There are two non-hero units included in this set, the @Civilian and @Dark_Templar_Hero.

        Returns:
        true if this unit type is a hero type, and false otherwise.

      • isPowerup

        public boolean isPowerup()
        Checks if this unit type is a powerup. Powerups can be picked up and carried by workers. They are usually only seen in campaign maps and @Capture_the_flag.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is a powerup type, and false otherwise.

      • isBeacon

        public boolean isBeacon()
        Checks if this unit type is a beacon. Each race has exactly one beacon each. They are Special_Zerg_Beacon, Special_Terran_Beacon, and Special_Protoss_Beacon.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is one of the three race beacons, and false otherwise.
        See Also:
        isFlagBeacon()

      • isFlagBeacon

        public boolean isFlagBeacon()
        Checks if this unit type is a flag beacon. Each race has exactly one flag beacon each. They are Special_Zerg_Flag_Beacon, Special_Terran_Flag_Beacon, and Special_Protoss_Flag_Beacon. Flag beacons spawn a @Flag after some ARBITRARY I FORGOT AMOUNT OF FRAMES.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is one of the three race flag beacons, and false otherwise.
        See Also:
        isBeacon()

      • isSpecialBuilding

        public boolean isSpecialBuilding()
        Checks if this structure is special and cannot be obtained normally within the game.
        Returns:
        true if this structure is a special building, and false otherwise.

      • isSpell

        public boolean isSpell()
        Identifies if this unit type is used to complement some @abilities. These include Spell_Dark_Swarm, Spell_Disruption_Web, and Spell_Scanner_Sweep, which correspond to TechType.Dark_Swarm, TechType.Disruption_Web, and TechType.Scanner_Sweep respectively.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is used for an ability, and false otherwise.

      • producesCreep

        public boolean producesCreep()
        Checks if this structure type produces creep. That is, the unit type spreads creep over a wide area so that @Zerg structures can be placed on it.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type spreads creep.
        Since:
        4.1.2

      • producesLarva

        public boolean producesLarva()
        Checks if this unit type produces larva. This is essentially used to check if the unit type is a @Hatchery, @Lair, or @Hive.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type produces larva.

      • isMineralField

        public boolean isMineralField()
        Checks if this unit type is a mineral field and contains a resource amount. This indicates that the unit type is either Resource_Mineral_Field, Resource_Mineral_Field_Type_2, or Resource_Mineral_Field_Type_3.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is a mineral field resource.

      • isCritter

        public boolean isCritter()
        Checks if this unit type is a neutral critter.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type is a critter, and false otherwise.

      • canBuildAddon

        public boolean canBuildAddon()
        Checks if this unit type is capable of constructing an add-on. An add-on is an extension or attachment for Terran structures, specifically the Command_Center, Factory, Starport, and Science_Facility.
        Returns:
        true if this unit type can construct an add-on, and false if it can not.
        See Also:
        isAddon()

      • buildsWhat

        public List<UnitType> buildsWhat()
        Retrieves the set of units that this unit type is capable of creating. This includes training, constructing, warping, and morphing.

        Some maps have special parameters that disable construction of units that are otherwise normally available. Use Player.isUnitAvailable(bwapi.UnitType) to determine if a unit type is actually available in the current game for a specific player.

        Returns:
        List of UnitTypes containing the units it can build.
        Since:
        4.1.2
        See Also:
        Player.isUnitAvailable(bwapi.UnitType)

      • researchesWhat

        public List<TechType> researchesWhat()
        Retrieves the set of technologies that this unit type is capable of researching.

        Some maps have special parameters that disable certain technologies. Use Player.isResearchAvailable(bwapi.TechType) to determine if a technology is actually available in the current game for a specific player.

        Returns:
        List of TechTypes containing the technology types that can be researched.
        Since:
        4.1.2
        See Also:
        Player.isResearchAvailable(bwapi.TechType)

      • upgradesWhat

        public List<UpgradeType> upgradesWhat()
        Retrieves the set of upgrades that this unit type is capable of upgrading.

        Some maps have special upgrade limitations. Use Player.getMaxUpgradeLevel(bwapi.UpgradeType) to check if an upgrade is available.

        Returns:
        List of UpgradeTypes containing the upgrade types that can be upgraded.
        Since:
        4.1.2
        See Also:
        Player.getMaxUpgradeLevel(bwapi.UpgradeType)

      • isSuccessorOf

        public boolean isSuccessorOf(UnitType type)
        Checks if the current type is equal to the provided type, or a successor of the provided type. For example, a Hive is a successor of a Hatchery, since it can still research the @Burrow technology.
        Parameters:
        type - The unit type to check.
        Since:
        4.2.0
        See Also:
        TechType.whatResearches(), UpgradeType.whatUpgrades()
